### Fix 3 — DATABASE_URL special characters (P3)
Originally a single builder bug — expanded to a 9-file fix after red team
found the same pattern (raw `parsed.password`, no `unquote()`, no
`quote_plus()`) in 9 other call sites plus a divergent regex parser.

- **Builders**: `DatabaseConfigBuilder.{postgresql, mysql}` and
  `AsyncDatabaseConfigBuilder.{postgresql, mysql}` (added `.mysql` — was
  missing) now URL-encode credentials via `quote_plus`
- **MySQL runtime parsers**: `db/connection.py::_init_mysql` and
  `trust/esa/database.py::_init_mysql` now use `urlparse` + `unquote` +
  null-byte defense (rejects `\x00` after decode — auth-bypass defense)
- **Replaced**: hand-rolled MySQL regex parser in `trust/esa/database.py`
  (was `r"mysql://([^:]+):([^@]+)@([^:/]+):?(\d+)?/(.+)"` — rejected
  valid percent-encoded passwords)
- **Downstream `unquote` added** at 8 production sites:
  - `src/kailash/nodes/data/async_sql.py:1345-1346`
  - `packages/kailash-dataflow/src/dataflow/core/pool_utils.py:208-219`
  - `packages/kailash-dataflow/src/dataflow/adapters/connection_parser.py:52-66`
  - `packages/kaizen-agents/src/kaizen_agents/patterns/state_manager.py:320-356` (x2)
  - `packages/kaizen-agents/tests/integration/orchestration/manual_table_creation.py` (x2)
  - `packages/kailash-dataflow/tests/e2e/dataflow_alpha/test_complete_user_journey.py` (x2)
- **Masking consolidation**: `DatabaseConfig.get_masked_connection_string`
  rewritten on `urlparse`/`parse_qsl` (regex was fragile); `mask_url()` in
  `dataflow/utils/masking.py` extended to handle MongoDB replica-set URLs
  (comma-netloc) and query-string credentials; `mongodb.py` delegates to
  canonical `mask_url`; both Redis `_sanitize_url` helpers
  (`trust/rate_limit` + `nexus/auth/rate_limit`) upgraded to mask query
  strings with the full sensitive-key set
- **Sensitive-key alignment**: 6-key set `{password, sslpassword, sslkey,
  authtoken, token, apikey}` is held in 4 places — `database_config.py`,
  `dataflow/utils/masking.py`, and both Redis backends. An in-code
  comment at `database_config.py:160-166` warns that all four sites must
  be kept in sync (future drift will be caught by parametrized tests at
  `test_arbor_database_url_special_chars.py::TestArborDatabaseUrlMasking::test_masked_connection_string_masks_all_sensitive_query_keys`)
- **kailash-mcp logs**: `cache.py` and `advanced/subscriptions.py` had
  `f"... {redis_url}"` log lines that leaked credentials — rewritten as
  structured `"%s://%s%s"` format with urlparse (`rules/observability.md`
  MUST NOT "No unstructured f'...' log messages")

### Cleanup — 47 JWT test failures (nexus.auth deprecation)
`nexus.auth` is deprecated per SPEC-06, migrating to `kailash.trust.auth`.
The JWT crypto was extracted from `JWTMiddleware` into a `JWTValidator`
helper but the middleware tests were never updated — `_make_middleware`
helpers use `__new__` to bypass `__init__`, and the original test helpers
don't assign `mw._validator`, so every call to `mw.create_access_token`,
`mw.create_refresh_token`, `mw._verify_token`, `mw._create_user_from_payload`,
`mw._is_path_exempt` hit an `AttributeError`.

**Fix** (two parts):
1. Added four thin-delegate methods to `JWTMiddleware` at
   `packages/kailash-nexus/src/nexus/auth/jwt.py:282-308` — preserves the
   pre-SPEC-06 API surface for the deprecation window
2. Updated all 8 `_make_middleware` test helpers + 1 inline case to
   construct `mw._validator = JWTValidator(mw.config)` after the `__new__`
   bypass

**Result**: 475 passed, 1 skipped (was 428 passed, 47 failed) in the full
`packages/kailash-nexus/tests/unit/auth/` suite.

### Cleanup — dataflow mongodb lazy import
`packages/kailash-dataflow/src/dataflow/adapters/mongodb.py` imported
`motor.motor_asyncio` unconditionally at module top. Any project that
ran `from dataflow import DataFlow` without motor installed hit
`ModuleNotFoundError` on module load, not at connect time. Moved motor
imports to lazy (inside `MongoDBAdapter.connect()`) with a descriptive
`ImportError` message pointing at `pip install motor pymongo`.

### Cleanup — ModelRegistry LocalRuntime deprecation
`ModelRegistry` owns its `LocalRuntime` and releases it via
`close()` → `runtime.release()`. But `LocalRuntime.execute()` emitted a
deprecation warning on first call unless `_cleanup_registered` OR
`_is_context_managed` was set. The registry already manages the lifecycle
correctly — it just needed to tell the runtime. Fix:
`self.runtime._cleanup_registered = True` in `__init__` after constructing
the own-runtime path. Two earlier attempts (using `__enter__()` /
`__exit__()` around execute) caused a `coroutine 'wait_for' was never
awaited` RuntimeWarning and hung pytest — reverted in favor of the flag
assignment.

